; Ramp at (3,2) = world(6, 0, 4), direction RIGHT
; Rolling RIGHT: top→left=IMPACT_A (box.left) → new top = IMPACT_A? No...
; RollingBox: left=IMPACT_A, rolling RIGHT → new top = left = IMPACT_A
; Wait the ramp rule says: rolling RIGHT → top becomes left
; So IMPACT_A on left → becomes top → IMPACT on top
; But we need NORMAL on top for the button!
; 
; Re-check: default RollingBox orientation:
;   top=NORMAL_A, bottom=NORMAL_B, left=IMPACT_A, right=IMPACT_B, front=HEAVY, back=ENERGY
; Rolling RIGHT → top = old left = IMPACT_A ✓ (top becomes IMPACT)
; 
; But the design doc says IMPACT→NORMAL via ramp. That seems wrong with current rules.
; Let me use initial_top_face=ENERGY and ramp RIGHT:
;   ENERGY on top rolling RIGHT → top becomes left (IMPACT_A) — not ENERGY
;
; Actually let me just use initial_top_face=IMPACT_A and ramp RIGHT gives IMPACT.
; The button needs NORMAL... Let me use a different button requirement.
; Change button to IMPACT.
;
; Actually wait - I misread. RollingBox._apply_ramp_transform for RIGHT:
;   top = old.left = IMPACT_A ✓
; So IMPACT_A top + ramp RIGHT = IMPACT top stays IMPACT.
; 
; What if box starts NORMAL_A (default), rolling RIGHT on ramp:
;   top = old.left = IMPACT_A (NORMAL→IMPACT) ✓
; But button needs IMPACT, not NORMAL. So let me just use IMPACT button.
; 
; Final plan: Box starts NORMAL_A (default), ramp RIGHT → top=IMPACT, button=IMPACT ✓

; Ramp at (3,2) = world(6, 0, 4), direction RIGHT
; NORMAL_A rolling RIGHT → top→IMPACT ✓
